> So how do I know if it's safe to use NoClick with my drive(s)?

Try it. There are probably only a few drives that have problems. None
of the Commodore-supplied drives should have problems, and I've never
heard about any NoClick-problems. I just happen to know that there are
drives that can't noclick, since I have one -:(

If use NoClick, and your drive starts making "ugly noises" (i.e. the
clicking sounds ugly), you're out of luck. To get the drive back
in shape, turn off the HD and insert a bootable disk and reboot --- if it
doesn't work, take out the disk, reset, wait until the drives clicks once,
insert disk. If it doesn't work, try again, maybe waiting two clicks
instead of one... after a few tries, it's probably okay. If you can't
get it to work, open the case and move the head manually.

Christian


